Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of Natural Language Processing (NLP) for building a dataset of folksonomy tags and suggests a new concept structure called "Folksodriven" to represent folksonomies. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories such as Information Retrieval (cs.IR) as it deals with organizing and retrieving information, Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it uses NLP techniques, Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as it discusses the network structure of folksonomy tags, Digital Libraries (cs.DL) as it deals with knowledge management systems, and Databases (cs.DB) as it involves the analysis of a dataset.
